# IDE Adapter Rule

All code that behaves differently per IDE (Cursor, VS Code, Trae, ...) **must** live in `app/src/ide-adapters/`.

## Never do this

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — IDE branch outside ide-adapters/
if (vscode.env.appName.includes('cursor')) {
  writeCursorMcpConfig(...);
} else {
  writeVsCodeMcpConfig(...);
}
```

## Always do this

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — call through the adapter
await getIdeAdapter().registerMcp(credPath, serverPath);
```

## Adding a new IDE

1. Create `app/src/ide-adapters/{ide-name}.ts` implementing `IdeAdapter` from `types.ts`.
2. Add one detection branch in `app/src/ide-adapters/index.ts`.
3. Update `app/src/ide-adapters/README.md` adapter table.

See `app/src/ide-adapters/README.md` for full documentation.
